=== Facilities Directly Over Source Springs ===
In most cases, water from source springs is piped or channeled to bathing facilities. However, some naturally discharging springs are located directly under bathing facilities (called ashi-moto-yushutsu). This is only possible if the spring's temperature is close to optimal for bathing. Such springs are relatively rare due to narrow temperature ranges. Examples include:

* '''Hokkaido:''' {{ill|Niseko Yakushi Onsen|ja|ニセコ薬師温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Aomori:''' {{ill|Sukayu Onsen|ja|酸ヶ湯温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Akita:''' {{ill|Nyūtō Onsenkyō|ja|乳頭温泉郷|12=draft|12=draft}}, including {{ill|Tsurunoyu Onsen|ja|鶴の湯温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Gunma:''' {{ill|Shiriyaki Onsen|ja|尻焼温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Hōshi Onsen|ja|法師温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Toyama:''' {{ill|Kanezuri Onsen|ja|鐘釣温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Wakayama:''' {{ill|Kawayu Onsen (Wakayama)|ja|川湯温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Okayama:''' {{ill|Yubara Onsen|ja|湯原温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}
* '''Ōita:''' {{ill|Myoban Onsen|ja|明礬温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}'s mud baths
* '''Kumamoto:''' {{ill|Jigoku Onsen|ja|地獄温泉|12=draft|12=draft}}

