=== Facilities Directly Over Source Springs ===
In most cases, water from source springs is piped or channeled to bathing facilities. However, some naturally discharging springs are located directly under bathing facilities (called ashi-moto-yushutsu). This is only possible if the spring's temperature is close to optimal for bathing. Such springs are relatively rare due to narrow temperature ranges. Examples include:

* '''Hokkaido:''' {{ill|Niseko Yakushi Onsen|ja|ニセコ薬師温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Niseko Yakushi Onsen|qq=}}
* '''Aomori:''' {{ill|Sukayu Onsen|ja|酸ヶ湯温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sukayu Onsen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 酸ヶ湯}}
* '''Akita:''' [[:en:Nyūtō Onsen|Nyūtō Onsenkyō]], including {{ill|Tsurunoyu Onsen|ja|鶴の湯温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsurunoyu Onsen|qq=}}
* '''Gunma:''' {{ill|Shiriyaki Onsen|ja|尻焼温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiriyaki Onsen|qq=}}, {{ill|Hōshi Onsen|ja|法師温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hōshi Onsen|qq=}}
* '''Toyama:''' {{ill|Kanezuri Onsen|ja|鐘釣温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanezuri Onsen|qq=}}
* '''Wakayama:''' {{ill|Kawayu Onsen (Wakayama)|ja|川湯温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawayu Onsen (Wakayama)|qq=}}
* '''Okayama:''' {{ill|Yubara Onsen|ja|湯原温泉|1=Yubara Onsen|2=ja|3=湯原温泉|4=ceb|5=Yubara hotspring|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yubara Onsen|13=User:Immanuelle/Yubara Onsen|qq=}}
* '''Ōita:''' {{ill|Myoban Onsen|ja|明礬温泉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Myoban Onsen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 別府温泉}}'s mud baths
